    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1915-01-20">January 20, 1915.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear <persName key="margaret_anderson">Miss Anderson</persName>:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram is just received. I am sending you two poems to choose from.
                <title>“Bright Sunlight”</title> is merely charming, as you see. <title>“Ely Cathedral”</title> is perhaps a
                little strong even for you; it is dealt at a formal, lip religion, so prevalent
                not only in <placeName key="england">England</placeName> but all over the world. I do not imagine you will want them
                both, in which case will you be so kind as to return the one you do not use.</p>
                <p>I had such a pleasant time on the train with your friend, <persName>Mr. Langner</persName>. And by the same
                token I enclose a check for <measure type="dollars" quantity="10">ten dollars</measure> as a little donation toward your <title key="littleReview" level="j">Magazine</title>,
                <measure type="cents" quantity="30">thirty cents</measure> of which I owe you, and please take it out.</p> 
                <p>In tearing haste,</p>
                <closer>Very sincerely,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
